[Preventive measures](https://www.quebec.ca/en/health/health-issues/a-z/general-information-about-coronavirus/#c53183) that apply to the general public also apply to children.
Even if their [symptoms](https://www.quebec.ca/en/health/health-issues/a-z/general-information-about-coronavirus/#c46539) are mild, children may be contagious. It is recommended to keep your children at home.
**Call your family doctor or** [**1 877 644‑4545**](tel:+1-877-644%E2%80%914545) if your child has one or more of the following symptoms :
*   Fever;
*   headache;
*   difficulty breathing;
*   new cough;
*   cough that gets worse.
To find out what to do when your child has a fever, go to the [Fever section in the guide From Tiny Tot to Toddler: from pregnancy to age two](https://www.inspq.qc.ca/en/tiny-tot/health/common-health-problems/fever) .

